        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_b/{size}/2130_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-25T04:03:19.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I had to pick this up on a Binny\u2019s closeout for $50.  2013 had me concerned over quality.  Thankfully, this bottle more than delivered.  The power, distinction, and concentration could go toe-to-toe with many a decent bottle of Corton Charlemagne. Elegantly refined, aromas of white flowers and oily stone fruits leap from the glass.  On the palate, there\u2019s straw, beeswax, pears, and lemon oil.  The acidity, while high, is perfectly balanced by a round, weighty finish.  This particular bottle was very fresh for 5 years past the vintage, but I certainly wouldn\u2019t chance waiting on any more bottles if I had them, especially if I was paying full retail.  93+ points.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
