      {
        "id": 2437750,
        "name": "Mark B",
        "username": "Mark_B",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/mark_b/{size}/2130_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-06-25T13:45:35.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Howard Cooper\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Howard Cooper:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Mark B\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Mark B:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>2013 had me concerned over quality.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Why?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Not saying this is the be-all-end-all, but a quick check of JR\u2019s website is saying 2013 was quite erratic with careful grape selection holding paramount to a producer\u2019s success.<br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/4/1/41fff83fcac6e12612c58f46626fed8a08d4481d.png\" alt=\"01634CAC-A155-4642-96EC-226E1C2E1E05.png\" data-base62-sha1=\"9pRrMOofNXEejPHPcRSSmPXAZD7\" width=\"270\" height=\"480\"></p>",
